ory path relative to repo root (default: '.')\\\"},\\n          \\\"recursive\\\": {\\\"type\\\": \\\"boolean\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"List recursively up to depth 3 (default: false)\\\"}\\n        }\\n      }\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"name\\\": \\\"search_code\\\",\\n      \\\"description\\\": \\\"Search for a regex pattern in files. Returns matching lines with file paths and line numbers.\\\",\\n      \\\"function_path\\\": \\\"spark.tools.search_code.execute\\\",\\n      \\\"parameters_schema\\\": {\\n        \\\"type\\\": \\\"object\\\",\\n        \\\"properties\\\": {\\n          \\\"pattern\\\": {\\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Regex pattern to search for\\\"},\\n          \\\"file_pattern\\\": {\\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Glob pattern to filter files (e.g. '*.py')\\\"},\\n          \\\"path\\\": {\\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Directory to search in (default: repo root)\\\"}\\n        },\\n        \\\"required\\\": [\\\"pattern\\\"]\\n      }\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"name\\\": \\\"get_file_tree\\\",\\n      \\\"description\\\": \\\"Get the full file tree of the repository as indented text. Respects .gitignore.\\\",\\n      \\\"function_path\\\": \\\"spark.tools.get_file_tree.execute\\\",\\n      \\\"parameters_schema\\\": {\\n        \\\"type\\\": \\\"object\\\",\\n        \\\"properties\\\": {\\n          \\\"max_depth\\\": {\\\"type\\\": \\\"integer\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Maximum directory depth (default: 4)\\\"},\\n          \\\"include_hidden\\\": {\\\"type\\\": \\\"boolean\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Include dotfiles/dotdirs (default: false)\\\"}\\n        }\\n      }\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"name\\\": \\\"get_db_state\\\",\\n      \\\"description\\\": \\\"Query the Spark SQLite database for file states, documented files, or stale files.\\\",\\n      \\\"function_path\\\": \\\"spark.tools.get_db_state.execute\\\",\\n      \\\"parameters_schema\\\": {\\n        \\\"type\\\": \\\"object\\\",\\n        \\\"properties\\\": {\\n          \\\"query\\\": {\\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"enum\\\": [\\\"documented_files\\\", \\\"stale_files\\\", \\\"all_files\\\", \\\"undocumented_files\\\"], \\\"description\\\": \\\"What to query\\\"}\\n        },\\n        \\\"required\\\": [\\\"query\\\"]\\n      }\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"name\\\": \\\"update_rules_index\\\",\\n      \\\"description\\\": \\\"Add or update an entry in a RULES_INDEX.md file.\\\",\\n      \\\"function_path\\\": \\\"spark.tools.update_rules_index.execute\\\",\\n      \\\"parameters_schema\\\": {\\n        \\\"type\\\": \\\"object\\\",\\n        \\\"properties\\\": {\\n          \\\"index_path\\\": {\\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Path to RULES_INDEX.md relative to repo root\\\"},\\n          \\\"entry_path\\\": {\\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Relative path to the rule file from the index\\\"},\\n          \\\"summary\\\": {\\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"One-line summary for the index entry\\\"},\\n          \\\"section\\\": {\\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Section heading to place the entry under (e.g. 'Documentation Rules')\\\"}\\n        },\\n        \\\"required\\\": [\\\"index_path\\\", \\\"entry_path\\\", \\\"summary\\\"]\\n      }\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"name\\\": \\\"ask_user\\\",\\n      \\\"description\\\": \\\"Ask the user a question in the terminal. Returns their answer. Supports default values (user presses Enter to accept).\\\",\\n      \\\"function_path\\\": \\\"spark.tools.ask_user.execute\\\",\\n      \\\"parameters_schema\\\": {\\n        \\\"type\\\": \\\"object\\\",\\n        \\\"properties\\\": {\\n          \\\"question\\\": {\\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"The question to display to the user\\\"},\\n          \\\"default\\\": {\\\"type\\\": \\\"string\\\", \\\"description\\\": \\\"Default value shown in brackets,