odemunch-core: JCodeMunch MCP server core: server entry point, configuration, security, watcher, path mapping, reindex state, and hook events.\n- jcodemunch-parser: JCodeMunch code parser subsystem: symbol extraction, language support, imports analysis, complexity metrics, hierarchy, SQL preprocessing, and context providers (dbt, git blame).\n- jcodemunch-storage: JCodeMunch storage layer: SQLite store, index store, embedding store, and token tracking.\n- jcodemunch-summarizer: JCodeMunch summarization subsystem: file-level and batch summarization of code.\n- jcodemunch-tools: JCodeMunch MCP tool implementations: 40+ analysis tools including search, indexing, dependency graphs, dead code detection, blast radius, refactoring safety checks, and more.\n- jcodemunch-tests: JCodeMunch test suite: 70+ test files covering all tools, parsers, storage, configuration, and integration scenarios.\n- jcodemunch-docs-and-config: JCodeMunch documentation, benchmarks, CI/CD workflows, and project configuration files.\n- root-files-and-templates: Top-level project files (CLAUDE.md, file_merger utility, commands, version marker) and the legacy HTML templates directory for the web UI.\n\n## Instructions\n\nAnalyze all files matching your area's patterns. Return a JSON report with `area`, `files`, `area_summary`, `cross_area_refs`, and optionally `suggested_splits`."
