    "content": "## Your Area Assignment\n\n**Area:** jcodemunch-tests\n**Description:** JCodeMunch test suite: 70+ test files covering all tools, parsers, storage, configuration, and integration scenarios.\n**File patterns:** [\"spark/vendors/jcodemunch/tests/**/*\"]\n\n## Plan Summary\n\nAreas in the plan:\n- spark-core: Core Spark package: initialization, orchestration, configuration, database, UI, and supporting modules that form the main application entry points.\n- spark-engine: Spark's agentic engine: the LLM loop, OpenRouter integration, tool execution, knowledge system, and runner that drives multi-agent documentation generation.\n- spark-agents-and-prompts: Agent definitions (JSON configs) and their corresponding prompt templates (Markdown) that define the behavior of planner, explorer, doc_writer, relationship_mapper, library, and onboarding agents.\n- spark-tools: Tool implementations available to Spark agents: file I/O, code search, library management, plugin installation, database state inspection, and the tool registry/definitions.\n- spark-library: Spark's plugin/library system: catalog of available plugins and library module initialization.\n- spark-templates: Template files that Spark installs into target repositories: .claude config templates, agentic framework templates (engine, tools, rules, skills, workflows), and app-module templates.\n- agentic-engine: The top-level agentic framework (installed instance): engine loop, OpenRouter client, tool executor, knowledge system, and runner.\n- agentic-tools: Tool implementations for the top-level agentic framework: file tree, directory listing, file read/write, code search, and tool definitions.\n- agentic-rules-skills-workflows: Agentic framework documentation rules, skill definitions, and workflow configurations at the top level.\n- claude-config: Claude Code configuration: rules (bug-fixing, invariants, testing), skills (code-documenter, code-search), spark plans, settings, and the rules index.\n- jcodemunch-core: JCodeMunch MCP server core: server entry point, configuration, security, watcher, path mapping, reindex state, and hook events.\n- jcodemunch-parser: JCodeMunch code parser subsystem: symbol extraction, language support, imports analysis, complexity metrics, hierarchy, SQL preprocessing, and context providers (dbt, git blame).\n- jcodemunch-storage: JCodeMunch storage layer: SQLite store, index store, embedding store, and token tracking.\n- jcodemunch-summarizer: JCodeMunch summarization subsystem: file-level and batch summarization of code.\n- jcodemunch-tools: JCodeMunch MCP tool implementations: 40+ analysis tools including search, indexing, dependency graphs, dead code detection, blast radius, refactoring safety checks, and more.\n- jcodemunch-tests: JCodeMunch test suite: 70+ test files covering all tools, parsers, storage, configuration, and integration scenarios.\n- jcodemunch-docs-and-config: JCodeMunch documentation, benchmarks, CI/CD workflows, and project configuration files.\n- root-files-and-templates: Top-level project files (CLAUDE.md, file_merger utility, commands, version marker) and the legacy HTML templates directory for the web UI.\n\n## Instructions\n\nAnalyze all files matching your area's patterns. Return a JSON report with `area`, `files`, `area_summary`, `cross_area_refs`, and optionally `suggested_splits`."
